Package magellan.library.utils

Class TagMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • magellan.library.utils.TagMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String>
    @Deprecated
public class TagMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String>
    Deprecated.
    (stm) Nobody seems to really need this class. A simple Map would do. The implementation is very inefficient.
    I'm not really sure why this class is here. It implements Map. It's probably just a pre-java-1.5 typesafe variant plus the getTag and putTag methods. entrySet() returns null and equals() always returns false.
